                          "Children": [
                            {
                              "$type": "Models.Memo, Models",
                              "Text": "Conidia are asexual propagules produced by the fungus in pycnidia on infected plant tissue, but not in the soil or debris directly.\n\nThey can persist for some time, but are subject to mortality from:\n\n- Desiccation\n\n- Microbial antagonism\n\n- UV exposure\n\n- Other environmental factors\n\nThe \"population\" of conidia in this pool **declines** over time due to these mortality factors.\n\nNew conidia are **added** from infected plants or **removed** into the debris or plants by rain splash.",
                              "Name": "Memo",
                              "ResourceName": null,
                              "Children": [],
                              "Enabled": true,
                              "ReadOnly": false
                            },
